parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy to cushion the impact.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbags do not deploy in a crash
the passenger seatbelt airbag sensor wire is damaged or cut.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Passenger Seatbelt Airbag Sensor Wire Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger seatbelt airbag sensor wire can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the airbags not deploying in a crash, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The passenger seatbelt airbag sensor wire is damaged or cut
the airbag warning light illuminates
the airbags do not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag module can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the airbags not deploying in a crash, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbags do not deploy in a crash
the dealership informs the consumer that there is no module installed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk violently, stall, or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks violently
thrusts forward

or stalls while driving; the transmission slips out of gear or drags; the vehicle makes a loud noise followed by a fast jerking motion; the transmission slips in low gears with low acceleration; the engine runs at high RPM at highway speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the fuel system can cause fuel to spill out onto the ground, leading to a potential fire hazard and environmental damage.
symptoms: Fuel shoots back out while fueling
fuel spills out onto the ground
difficulty filling the fuel tank
taking multiple attempts to fill the tank
and the fuel gauge not accurately displaying the fuel level.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking of the accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unintentionally, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks or catches
the vehicle accelerates unintentionally
and the pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The slipping of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power or stalls
and the transmission does not engage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the instrument cluster can cause the speedometer, tachometer, and other gauges to display inaccurate or erratic readings, leading to confusion and potential accidents.
symptoms: The speedometer drops to zero and then recalibrates to the new speed
the tachometer displays incorrect readings
and the gauges malfunction or display erratic readings.
